comment:
* This class iterates over set of nodes that needs to be sorted.
 * @xsl.usage internal

variables.name: m_inNaturalOrderStatic
variables.comment:
True if the nodes will be found in document order, and this can 
   * be determined statically.

methods.name: public boolean isDocOrdered()
methods.comment:
* Returns true if all the nodes in the iteration well be returned in document 
   * order.
   * 
   * @return true as a default.

methods.name: boolean canBeWalkedInNaturalDocOrderStatic()
methods.comment:
* Tell if the nodeset can be walked in doc order, via static analysis. 
   *
   *
   * @return true if the nodeset can be walked in doc order, without sorting.

methods.name: public void fixupVariables(java.util.Vector vars, int globalsSize)
methods.comment:
* This function is used to perform some extra analysis of the iterator.
   * 
   * @param vars List of QNames that correspond to variables.  This list 
   * should be searched backwards for the first qualified name that 
   * corresponds to the variable reference qname.  The position of the 
   * QName in the vector from the start of the vector will be its position 
   * in the stack frame (but variables above the globalsTop value will need 
   * to be offset to the current stack frame).

methodNames: public void fixupVariables(java.util.Vector vars, int globalsSize)
